cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about integrating relation constraints with neural networks for relation extraction, which is a task in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new loss term and develops efficient methods, which involve machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also deals with inconsistency among predictions, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR), indicating that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category. Finally, the paper focuses on relation extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing and machine learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a plausible category as well.
